values: What I'm about to write has no meaning or signifigance, its merely mildly interesting. Perhaps a little more so for people interested in how the human body works. Well. I had a zit on my nose. And while applying pressure to it to force its nasty contents out a hair came out from my nose root first. As far as I can guess a hair from inside my nise has passed to the outside via the zit. I found it mildly shocking. The good news is the zit is gone now. Why won't puberty end??

Well Cuba was alright. Did alot of reading. Building Sandcastles. Eating. Dancing. And the like. Also, I just found out my trip to New York city leaves 12:15 AM! of the 3rd. So It seems I'm not even home for 24 hours before I ship out again. Its exciting. Things to say: Neil Gaiman is an amazing author as with William Gibson and Bruce Sterling. I'm really not one for sharing at the moment. The curious should inquire. Good night, happy new years.

Ok, heres the pitch. Its a story about two guys at a party. One is chasing a girl where the other is running from a scary ex who is chasing him. And since it's science fiction it looks at how nano technology has affected a group of californians who live on the moon. It delves into how they live, where they live, the things they do, the things they care about, the drugs they use and yes the sex they have. Oh, and the catch is that the two guys are CalTech grads who ushered in the nanotech/information age by creating a clever program for the university's nano assembler to create more self recreating nanoassemblers that woud sneak into people's houses at nigtht, eat the washing machine and create  a dozen more nano assemblers that would repeat the process.(nano assemblers being hugely expensive no one cared for the loss of a major applience). But no one remembers or believes it was the two guys in the story that did this. Of course I have more ideas tagged to this but I don't need to mention them. Inquire for more information, motivation might be nice and hopefully I complete this short story.

Perhaps its rude to "blog" only to kill a few minutes, but thats tuff for all you out there on the internet. Hmmm. Exams, nearly done. I think have and will continue to go very well. Life is grand, the food is good, the conversation riviting. Yea.. I got nothin to share with the world. Nothing deep and inspiring or even interesting to anyone but myself. Just remember, the universe isn't governed by mathmatics, the universe governs mathmatics. Very powerful difference there. Well, catch you all on the flip side.

"What to do with this space?" Is the problem that plagued me for some time. A rehash of current events is silly, and talking about the news is a) boring and b) impossible as I don't have the time to follow the news anymore.


So.. I was using the urinal the other day and the guy next to me started beat boxing. For years I thought the most awkward thing is for the guy the next urinal over to do is talk to me or if he peaked, but no, Mr. Beatz trumped them all. It was a sick tune however. 

Engineering Science students fall into to categories now. Insane and suicidal. Neither sounds very good, I'm glad I'm a civ. 

Segwaying now, the video game CIV IV is bad. When will developers learn that Good 2D graphics beat out shitty 3D?? Oh well, back to CIV III for me. 

Something witty and wise? Hmmm ~strokes beard~ Ah, an anecdote perhaps. Today to idiots were wrestling on the subway platform over a disagreement about a phone. They were utterly unaware about the social stigma of fighting in public not to mention the danger of those fast moving metal objects that move at high speeds through the tunnels. Many of the people at the station stopped to watch them fight while an old lady tried to talk them out of it. I however kept reading my book. My question to those who may read this, does that story say more about the delinquents, the old lady or me?

My mother left for New York this morning, she took with her one of my neighbors. Well that means two families without mothers/wives left without thanksgiving dinner. But all hope was not lost. My neighber who we'll call Bryan was primed and ready to pick up the slack. He put together a suprisingly excellent turkey dinner. It's sorta hard to explain the scenerio, but its best to imagine it from the perspective of my father and Bryan. The wives left and it was up to them to make their own thanksgiving dinner. Just interesting.

Art no longer is about skill with a paint brush or the emotion portrayed in images. No its about extremism, and the Italians just raised that bar. It seems a giant wool pink bunny rabbit on the side of a mountain constitutes good art these days. And by god its interactive too, as you can climb it and rest of its soft pink belly knitted by teams of old ladies in the sweater mines. And you know what, I'm going to go to that damn mountain and climb that damn rabbit and bloody well take a nap on all its soft woolly glory. Who's with me?!

See http://www.ananova.com/news/story/sm_1541732.html?menu= for story and picture.

Well I'm jacked up on caffine and sugar because of a scavenger hunt challenge. And As i walked home from the bus utterly awake and able to hear and see better than ever before It occured to me that recounting the amazing last few days could only cheapen them. Te things that happened should be shared in person and over a good drink. Infact I think I might give up these sterile re-hashes of the odd adventures that I get myself in (or better yet happen without my planning). Other important realisations: Life is men to be shared with flesh and blood people, caffine should be elected into the state of a demi god, and something about priorities and human contact... Well for the three people who read this, expect to see me in person soon. It's best that way.

I realize that the Adventures of Tim are hardly very interesting, and only mildly funny at the best of times. Non of it really needs any comment or thought. SO I think I'll start a new blog so I can discuss current news, tech, and ideas. Perhaps Views of Tim, or Opinions of Tim. New Orleans is a good topic of discussion, as well as the feasibility of uploading minds. Look forward to it in the future.

Hell Waldo Watchers. I've been circling town on the L train getting a glimpse of the tall buildings before heading to the Museum of Science and Industry. Where I rode the real trains I saw the model ones circle around a huge display. The rest of the museum was severely lacking, though the U bout was sorta cool. I also dined in the upscale Walnut Room for lunch, then the Lowscale Burnellie's for dinner. I've gone high to low, from big to small today. Have you found my sunglasses yet?

Hello from the Windy City, a city that has really earned its name today as I struggled to keep me hat on my head. But my sunglasses did manage to get away from me. Can you Waldo Watchers spot them? Today I saw all mannor of interesting and exotic fish and animals, like the Rock Lobster and Monkey Frog. I also saw a Pier that had a New Orlean's themed Restaraunt. The food was great though a tad wet (bad joke I know). Chicago is an amazingly run city and in the top five for best in the world. See you next page.

Greetings Waldo watchers. I'm reporting from the great city of production as part of my around the world hike (not really just with the rents)and I've seen some amazing things like the worlds tallest building (if you count the antenna) and giant reflective bean. See if you can spot me at each of the locations I go to (try using google maps and hope the satalite was in the right place at the right time) and I'll continue to report in on the day's events. Also, if anyone knows what a good souvenir might be let me know. I'm really at a loss.

For the first time in over seven years I'm unemployed. And couldn't be happier. It seems a certain customer knew I would be leaving tonight and left a perfectly good picture and picture frame for me to find and take home. Minus the glass. I also nicked my work gloves. I'm retired, nifty.
The last paper delivery is done. I'm now only two days away from unemployment and damn am I looking forward to it. Next, fix my camera then its on to day two of the Con.

After a near pointless hour and a half session at U of T about getting ready for school Ciara and I headed south and hoped a ferry for the island. Overall it was a good 15 km hike to find both geo caches. The second one was a challenge as we came at it in the wrong direction and got caught in a web of branches and thorns, not to mention all the ants. I got 5 or 6 bites. Took about 4 hours including the ferry rides and a solid yet not to strenuous walk. Also did the hedge maze and looked at the animals in the petting Zoo. It was fun.

On my lunch break from work. I saw I bolt of lightning up close. Very awesome. Ummm... thats all there is to report. That and I'm activily developing ideas for one or more stories. Maybe even do a story board for a cartoon of one of my ideas. The other is more fitting for a novel. I'm still planning on writing SF. All my little projects are creeping along right now, perhaps I need to dedicate myself to one or two things instead of tackling 5 five or six. I think I've rambled on enough.

I'm such a fucking mess. I feel like my insides have had an egg beater taken to them. It also seems I have yet another good example on how people leave at "a drop of a hat". Its becoming painfully clear that fucking up socially can not happen as theres seldom a second chance... well a third chance. Fuck. Just, bloody fucking hell. A joke goes bad at it seems Mon dissapeared. My only hope is that I'm crippling-ly paranoid, what a fucking useless kind of hope.
Tonight I had two of the most relaxing and fulsilling driving experiences. Almost every light was green, and the beach boys greatest hits set the modd perfectly... damn what a good night
Room = painted. All furnature descions and the armoir facade should be done in a matter of days. Then its the gecko... then life i suppose.

Current Projects: Renovate Room with Adventurer's Club theme
                  Find a place to learn sword fighting, probably kendo
                  Make Samurai Jack t-shirt
                  Costume for Convention, perhaps as Jack
                  Sky diving, but that might be on hold for now due to interest in swords
Friday I started to grow a beard. And I think I'm ready to shave it off, but someone told me "scruffy" was a good look for me. What to do...?

Shot some pool (played badly), drove around (with some of the guys), and wandered the bordwalk (after 11pm), went for a slice of pizza just after midnight (meaty pizza). It was a decent evening. Ran into a guy from school, which continues to prove that no matter where I go I seem to run into someone I know. The sky was red, I hate that. And thats about all there is to say.

Well Home Depot has finally gotten into my head. I now indulge my latest fetish. My newest bad habit. Yes I'm talking about buying cheap multi-tools. Before it was pliers with knives and screw driver bits in the handle. Today's sin is a hammer with some big blades in the handle. A FUCKING HAMMER. I'm not made of stone!! And the hammer is actuall a gripping tool and wire cutter! And theres a belt pouch thingy!! My god it's like they know everything I desire and bundle it into cheap utility. But hey.. its just $9. 

Now moving onto something more important. In one of our usual conversations about geochacheing and chainmail exotic clothing. The idea of doing a role playing geocaching adventure was arrived upon! Now I won't be reveiling to many details at "they" might be reading. Know this, it will be cool, awesome and funny. We'll be working on this idea more in the near future. RPGeocaching.. it will be the biggest thing to nerds/geeks since Star Trek conventions. Wait and see.

This makes another full and decent day. 5 hour shift at Home Depot, house work, good dinner. Then some friends came over for a game of RISK 2210 (or some such year). I came in second, it was a tough slog but I'll do better next time. Work and fun, a good balance.

I also saw Batman Begins tonight! I nearly forgot with all the excitement. It is hands down the best Batman movie, its very awesome despite a few technical errors. The car... SEXIEST THING I'VE EVER SEEN. And Christian Balle (or however his name is spelt) is the best Bruse Wayne ever, though I felt his  Batman appearances were a tad weak. I don't want to ruin the movie for anyone who hasn't seen it yet. But do see it. Its awesome. perhaps better.

I remember everything. Let that be known, its important. The full account of what occured will be drafted into a short story that will be mostly true to life, please allow artistic liberties. To forshadow the story I will begin roughly where I plan to start. At 9 something saturday morning I walked from Greg's house to mine still partially covered in my own vomit. I spent the night after vomiting on myself in Mihir's car, and vomiting on the side of his car, and greg's back yard. I had been drinking on the beach with some guys (and gals) I know. First time being drunk, what a time, what an interesting turn of events as I spent years fighting it. Before that beach party I shot some pool with Greg and Andrew, once standard stuff but rare once the friendship broke down. Its being rebuilt. Two reversals on personal policy in one night. But I remember everything.

I really should have mentioned this last night, but this morning when I'm on hold to talk to the Duty Manager for Home Depot is a good a time as any to write this. Well I've been accepted into U of T for engineering, specifically Civil. Now the minor issue, I know I want to go to U of T, but I'm not sure if I'm biased towards it due to the people I know who are there or will be going. I want to make the right choice, but not a biased choice... but U of T can be considered the best place for Civil Engineering... Well I'll attend their saturday information day, compare that with McMaster and then decide. But Queens isn't out of thr running yet! Hmmm I'll be pondering this further.
